We reiterated our prior year’s recommendations that Management:
Require all department heads authorized to issue Gasoline Withdrawal Slip (GWS) to prepare the Monthly Summary of the Daily Totals of GWS Issued of their respective department within three days after the end of each month, with the complete GWS and Charge Invoices attached as supporting documents, for submission to the GSO;
Direct the GSO to consolidate the Monthly Summary of Daily Totals of GWS Issued submitted by the other departments with its own Summary, and submit the consolidated report with its complete supporting documents, on or before the fifth day at the end of each month, to the City Accounting Office (CAO) for recording;
In addition, the GSO shall prepare the consolidated Monthly Fuel Consumption Report, for submission to the Auditor, thru the CAO, on or before the 10th day after the end of each month;
Direct the GSO to have the defective odometers of the City’s service vehicles repaired and to instruct the drivers of service vehicles to report immediately any defective odometer in order that the same may be repaired immediately.
Henceforth, we recommended that Management:
Use the required format of a serially numbered trip ticket duly approved by the Agency Head or the authorized representative for proper monitoring of fuel consumption;
Instruct the drivers of the LGU to accomplish properly the DTTs, to supply the relevant data in all the required fields, and to avoid unnecessary erasures to ensure the authenticity and reliability of data; and
Accomplish properly the Monthly Report on Fuel Consumption and ensure that the data specified therein are cross-checked with the supporting attachments for accurate reporting measures.

We recommended that Management:
Require the CHO to render a report to the Accountant on the receipt, issuance, and balances of vaccines and other inventories directly received from outside sources;
Instruct the CHO to prepare Requisition and Issue Slip for succeeding issuance of vaccines, to be forwarded to the GSO;
Require the GSO to consolidate the RIS received from the CHO, and prepare the SSMI to be forwarded to the Accounting for recording; and
Require the Accountant to record the cost of ending inventory of vaccines as at year-end and henceforth, recognize and record future receipts and issuance of the same.

We recommended the following:
Preparation of the quarterly and annual reports by the City Accountant using SEF Budget Accountability Form No. 1 (Annex B of DepEd-DBM-DILG Joint Memorandum Circular No. 1, s. 2017) on SEF utilization;
Coordination of the LSB with the City Accountant on the submission of quarterly and annual reports on SEF approved by the LCE, to the DepEd CO, copy furnished the Sangguniang Panlungsod and the Regional Offices of the DBM and DILG;
Require that the SEF budget shall be presented by program, activity and project by allotment, class per school using SEF Budget Preparation Form No. 1 (Section 5.2.2 of DepEd-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 1, s. 2017); and
Adherence to the prescribed format in presentation of SAAOB by presenting the PPAs’ complete details in the Functions/Program Project/Activity column in compliance with prescribed rules and regulations.

We reiterated out prior year’s audit recommendation that Management direct:

The City Treasurer to send written notices to the payees of unclaimed checks at least one month before a check becomes stale;

The City Accountant review the long outstanding stale checks and take up the necessary entry reversing to Cash-in bank and Accounts Payable the amounts thereof;

The City Treasurer to cancel the unclaimed stale checks and furnish the accountant with the original disbursement vouchers (DV) and its supporting documents, for the preparation of the Journal Voucher/s following the procedures set forth in the MNGAS for LGUs.

We recommended that Management:

Direct the City Accountant to secure the lacking supporting documents to the DVs from the concerned offices/ personnel and submit promptly to the Auditor, otherwise the non-submission thereof would warrant the issuance of Notice of Suspension/Disallowance; and; 

Require strict compliance by the City Accountant with pertinent provisions of PD No. 1445 and COA Circular No. 2012-001 to protect the interest of the government and prevent unwarranted disbursements of public funds.

For the deficiencies noted, we recommended that Management direct all concerned to:

Request from GSP Legazpi City liquidation report for the fund transfers/cash advances totaling ₱51,400.00 and to discontinue granting fund transfers that is contrary to laws, rules and regulations;

Initiate the refund of the payment made to BSP for the registration of Council Executive Board amounting ₱17,100.00;

Stop the practice of disbursing claims that cannot be categorized under “operation and maintenance of public schools”, thus, not allowed;

Furnish the Audit Team, supporting documents to the payroll, indicating the place of assignment of personnel paid under check no. 67525504 dated April 5, 2021; and

Henceforth, strictly adhere to the guidelines set on various DepEd-DBM-DILG Joint Circulars regarding the charging of expenses to SEF.

