This is a continuing program of OCENR to regularly monitor the implementation of SP Resolution No. 14-0272-2018

The OCENR did and still doing to follow SP Resolution No. 14-0272-2018 dated February 21, 2011 and among the activities/initiatives done are as follows:

The passage of Executive Order No. 18, s. 2012, Implementing the Anti-Plastic Ordinance of the Province of Albay in the City’s Public Market and Ambulant Vendors during Saturdays, Sundays and non-working Days;

Conduct of information, education and communication (IEC) campaign to public markets ambulant vendors, small business establishments and barangay within the city;

Implementation of the “Plastic for Rice” that encouraged the barangay through their Barangay Eco-Waste Managers and Eco Aides to separate the dry and clean plastics and convert/exchange it with rice at the OCENR.

