We recommended that Management:

Require the City Budget Office to make a systematic and realistic revenue forecasting taking into account prior years’ experiences and statistics as aids in setting targets;

Direct the City Budget Officer to undertake a review of the present budgeting process/activities done by the City Budget Office to set a clearer guide for the concerned revenue generating Departments toward attaining the target set;

Require the City Treasurer and other Departments involved in generating revenues to meet its targets by conducting periodic review of collection performance by concerned officials to ascertain whether collection targets are attained and to analyze the reasons for any shortfall in collections and to find solutions to minimize, reduce or avoid incurrence of shortfall in the future;

Require the City Budget Office to provide targets for revenue accounts without projected revenues by setting targets based on statistics, prior years’ experiences and future expectations; and

Require the City Treasurer and City Accountant to accomplish the Quarterly Report of Income (LBAc Form No. 1) on a periodic basis in order to monitor the status of revenue generation and at the same time adopt measures that will likely improve collection for accounts not reaching the targets, thus, provide assurance that more plans and programs will be fully implemented.

We recommended that Management:
Require the OIC-CDRRMC to coordinate with the OIC-City Engineer in ensuring that programmed Capital Outlay – Infrastructure projects for LDRRMF are monitored and are accomplished to avoid the ballooning balance of unexpended fund;




Require the OIC-CDRRMC and OIC-City Accountant to coordinate with each other in ensuring that utilization rate for the LDRRMF-Continuing Appropriation and STF be improved through constant monitoring of these LDRRMF, since both departments can determine possible sources of funds and have a clearer picture of the availability of unutilized funds that can be appropriated and made part of the available budgetary sources for the ensuing year;

